    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="305"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/7–1750</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Executive Secretary of the National Security
                        Council</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">National Security
                            Council</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-17">July 17,
                            1950</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Future United States Policy With Respect to North
                    Korea</p>
                <p>The President has requested the National Security Council to prepare for his
                    consideration a report on the subject, covering the policy which should be
                    pursued by the United States after the North Korean forces have been driven back
                    to the 38th parallel.</p>
                <p>Accordingly, this project is being referred to the <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> Staff for the preparation of a report for Council
                    consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
